1980;;Pray TV;;American;;Rick Friedberg;;Rosemary Alexander, Dabney Coleman;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pray_TV;;Failing UHF TV station KRUD, Channel 17, is "reborn" as Christian television station KGOD. The new format is a big success but attracts an incompatible mix of fringe ministries and broadcasters wanting time on the station. A series of humorous vignettes show the different religious shows the station broadcasts: a faith healer, a radical black nationalist preacher, a preacher with a drive-in church, a Christian game show, etc.<br><br>The film is very similar in both plot and style to the 1989 film UHF.[2][3]